body:
> would this address #330 and #348 (partially)?
>
> EDIT: Confirmed! Adding `StartupWMClass=Alacritty` to the end of my Alacritty.desktop file and saving it immediately fixes the icon issues mentioned in #330 without even restarting the process for me on Ubuntu 16.10. Commenting out that line and restarting alacritty #330 occurs again.

@brycefisher I confirm too it fixes #330 (just tested under Ubuntu 16.04.2). I doubt it fixes #348 though, as setting `StartupWMClass` has no impact on what `xprop` says about the Alacritty window (no x property of the window ends up mutated, it is only like a *read*-time level of indirection used by window matching logic).

> I actually have a patch for setting `wm_class separately`, but I decided against it since it's already set by the title. Should we set `wm_class` independently? Seems like that workaround would be fine.

@jwilm workaround sounds fine yeah; your call, you probably know more about me about this wm stuff to judge what's best.
